        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 9:21PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 921 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 14 miles west of Marshall to 3 miles north of
Hendersonville. Movement was northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Downtown Asheville, Marshall, Hendersonville, East Asheville, Arden,
West Asheville, North Asheville, Black Mountain, Woodfin, and
Fletcher.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
